# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: HollowWorld | Scene: TheHollowWorldWarrior5
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "When the next morning came, Sarah had found Samayra still in poor condition."
    new "When the next morning came, Sarah had found Samayra still in poor condition."

    old "For a brief moment, the girl had sought to fight Sarah on her decision, trying to still hide her sickness."
    new "For a brief moment, the girl had sought to fight Sarah on her decision, trying to still hide her sickness."

    old "No...I...I can still march...just for...today."
    new "No...I...I can still march...just for...today."

    old "She spoke with broken breaths."
    new "She spoke with broken breaths."

    old "Worst, Sarah could hear her lungs rattle each time she drewn in her breath."
    new "Worst, Sarah could hear her lungs rattle each time she drewn in her breath."

    old "It wasn't long before the girl was hunched over, exhausted merely from packing."
    new "It wasn't long before the girl was hunched over, exhausted merely from packing."

    old "You're going on the medical sled, that's an order."
    new "You're going on the medical sled, that's an order."

    old "Sarah grabbed Samayra by her upper arm and dragged her along."
    new "Sarah grabbed Samayra by her upper arm and dragged her along."

    old "They only made it a few steps before the girl's legs gave out."
    new "They only made it a few steps before the girl's legs gave out."

    old "Sarah caught her only just in time."
    new "Sarah caught her only just in time."

    old "Surprising herself, she pulled Samayra up and carried her in her arms."
    new "Surprising herself, she pulled Samayra up and carried her in her arms."

    old "Sarah could feel Samayra instinctively burying her head into Sarah's shoulder."
    new "Sarah could feel Samayra instinctively burying her head into Sarah's shoulder."

    old "You...you're a good friend...Sarah..."
    new "You...you're a good friend...Sarah..."

    old "The girl's voice faded."
    new "The girl's voice faded."

    old "Don't think about that for now. Just focus on getting better."
    new "Don't think about that for now. Just focus on getting better."

    old "But Sarah wasn't sure if the girl would get better. Very few made it back from the medical sled."
    new "But Sarah wasn't sure if the girl would get better. Very few made it back from the medical sled."

    old "Sarah carried Samayra through the camp in her arms, weaving through the crowds of soldiers that each seemed more occupied with their own work."
    new "Sarah carried Samayra through the camp in her arms, weaving through the crowds of soldiers that each seemed more occupied with their own work."

    old "When she finally arrived, Sarah's worries grew even deeper."
    new "When she finally arrived, Sarah's worries grew even deeper."

    old "Spread out across the medical sleds were soldiers, ailing, delirous with heat, or suffering from wounds that had never managed to heal."
    new "Spread out across the medical sleds were soldiers, ailing, delirous with heat, or suffering from wounds that had never managed to heal."

    old "Across the crowd, Sarah could hear a few lungs rattle as Samayra's did."
    new "Across the crowd, Sarah could hear a few lungs rattle as Samayra's did."

    old "Sarah felt Samayra's small and weak hands clutch her chest."
    new "Sarah felt Samayra's small and weak hands clutch her chest."

    old "Don't put me here...please..."
    new "Don't put me here...please..."

    old "Sarah wished there was another option."
    new "Sarah wished there was another option."

    old "I...you're sick, Samayra..."
    new "I...you're sick, Samayra..."

    old "I know...but...please, if you have to...can you stay with me?"
    new "I know...but...please, if you have to...can you stay with me?"

    old "I don't want to...not alone..."
    new "I don't want to...not alone..."

    old "Samayra didn't finish her sentence, but Sarah understood enough."
    new "Samayra didn't finish her sentence, but Sarah understood enough."

    old "Of course, Samayra, I'll be right here with you."
    new "Of course, Samayra, I'll be right here with you."

    old "Sarah placed Samayra down on one of the sleds, a bit distanced from the others."
    new "Sarah placed Samayra down on one of the sleds, a bit distanced from the others."

    old "Then she seized the reins of the sled and began to pull it herself."
    new "Then she seized the reins of the sled and began to pull it herself."

    old "Sarah wasn't sure if she had the energy for all this. Even an ordinary march was exhausting enough, but she also knew she didn't have the heart to leave the girl."
    new "Sarah wasn't sure if she had the energy for all this. Even an ordinary march was exhausting enough, but she also knew she didn't have the heart to leave the girl."

    old "Whatever else, she didn't deserve a fate that cruel, not after all she'd been through."
    new "Whatever else, she didn't deserve a fate that cruel, not after all she'd been through."

    old "All through the day, Sarah bore the weight of Samayra as though it was nothing to her."
    new "All through the day, Sarah bore the weight of Samayra as though it was nothing to her."

    old "What it costed her extra in effort, she made up for in spirit."
    new "What it costed her extra in effort, she made up for in spirit."

    old "Behind her, she could hear the girl wail and ache, at times softly sobbing."
    new "Behind her, she could hear the girl wail and ache, at times softly sobbing."

    old "She wanted to be so much more, but the nature of her body and its current condition made it not a question of strength, only one of cruel biology."
    new "She wanted to be so much more, but the nature of her body and its current condition made it not a question of strength, only one of cruel biology."

    old "And the truth was that the girl's build was too weak for a days hard work, and a days hard work was nothing compared to this march in the desert."
    new "And the truth was that the girl's build was too weak for a days hard work, and a days hard work was nothing compared to this march in the desert."

    old "Even strong and powerful men were being brought low. A girl like Samayra had no chance, no matter how much she tried."
    new "Even strong and powerful men were being brought low. A girl like Samayra had no chance, no matter how much she tried."

    old "Sarah felt a tear run past her face, knowing she would lose the poor girl."
    new "Sarah felt a tear run past her face, knowing she would lose the poor girl."

    old "Still, Sarah carried on, dragging the sled until night fell and the camp was set up again."
    new "Still, Sarah carried on, dragging the sled until night fell and the camp was set up again."

    old "Samayra for her part, had fought hard enough to survive yet one more day."
    new "Samayra for her part, had fought hard enough to survive yet one more day."

    old "When Sarah made a campfire and placed Samayra close to it for warmth, she heard the girl speak for the first time since she had put her on the medical sled."
    new "When Sarah made a campfire and placed Samayra close to it for warmth, she heard the girl speak for the first time since she had put her on the medical sled."

    old "W-w-water..."
    new "W-w-water..."

    old "The word barely made it past her cracked lips."
    new "The word barely made it past her cracked lips."

    old "Sarah brushed Samayra's face clean."
    new "Sarah brushed Samayra's face clean."

    old "Of course, I'm going to get you some water, you stay here."
    new "Of course, I'm going to get you some water, you stay here."

    old "The day passed by with little to remark on."
    new "The day passed by with little to remark on."

    old "Marching through the day, Sarah finally managed to get some rest when they made camp for the night."
    new "Marching through the day, Sarah finally managed to get some rest when they made camp for the night."

    old "Too focused on marching, she could feel her cracked lips, parched from lack of water."
    new "Too focused on marching, she could feel her cracked lips, parched from lack of water."

    old "Sarah set out to resolve the matter."
    new "Sarah set out to resolve the matter."

    old "Walking through the camp by herself, Sarah set out to find water."
    new "Walking through the camp by herself, Sarah set out to find water."

    old "They had marched on longer than usual, making up time by pushing themselves to keep going through the first hours of the night."
    new "They had marched on longer than usual, making up time by pushing themselves to keep going through the first hours of the night."

    old "As a result, the camp was buzzing with activity, soldiers working on unpacking and rigging the sleds to protect them from potential desert storms."
    new "As a result, the camp was buzzing with activity, soldiers working on unpacking and rigging the sleds to protect them from potential desert storms."

    old "Sarah turned down the direction where the foodstuffs were usually kept, but to her surprise found only more packs of soldiers, busily working."
    new "Sarah turned down the direction where the foodstuffs were usually kept, but to her surprise found only more packs of soldiers, busily working."

    old "Asking around, she received five different directions, each contradicting the other."
    new "Asking around, she received five different directions, each contradicting the other."

    old "Sarah sighed but kept looking for water."
    new "Sarah sighed but kept looking for water."

    old "Ask, follow, search, open up carts."
    new "Ask, follow, search, open up carts."

    old "Everywhere she went, the water was absent."
    new "Everywhere she went, the water was absent."

    old "By the end, Sarah had found herself near the edge of the camp, annoyed and frustrated by the chaos that seemed to have overtaken everything."
    new "By the end, Sarah had found herself near the edge of the camp, annoyed and frustrated by the chaos that seemed to have overtaken everything."

    old "They had once been so organized, so efficient."
    new "They had once been so organized, so efficient."

    old "The collapse of morale had done more than just suppress peoples humors, it had also begun to make them lazy."
    new "The collapse of morale had done more than just suppress peoples humors, it had also begun to make them lazy."

    old "That was a dangerous thing in a place like this."
    new "That was a dangerous thing in a place like this."

    old "Then, just as she was ready to turn around, Sarah heard the sound of running water."
    new "Then, just as she was ready to turn around, Sarah heard the sound of running water."

    old "For a moment, she considered herself mad. Water didn't flow like that in the desert..."
    new "For a moment, she considered herself mad. Water didn't flow like that in the desert..."

    old "But her ears did not deceive her, she heard it as sure as anything else."
    new "But her ears did not deceive her, she heard it as sure as anything else."

    old "If there isn't any water, I've surely lost my marbles..."
    new "If there isn't any water, I've surely lost my marbles..."

    old "Sarah mumbled to herself as she slid down the hill, towards the sound."
    new "Sarah mumbled to herself as she slid down the hill, towards the sound."

    old "Suddenly, the earth beneath her feet turned solid and hidden under a curve in the dune, Sarah saw the entrance to a cave."
    new "Suddenly, the earth beneath her feet turned solid and hidden under a curve in the dune, Sarah saw the entrance to a cave."

    old "Unable to suppress even a hint of hesitation, Sarah walked closer towards the entrance of the cave, still following the sound."
    new "Unable to suppress even a hint of hesitation, Sarah walked closer towards the entrance of the cave, still following the sound."

    old "Stepping into the cave, Sarah was instantly struck by the sense of relief she felt as cool air breezed past her skin."
    new "Stepping into the cave, Sarah was instantly struck by the sense of relief she felt as cool air breezed past her skin."

    old "More than cool, the air almost seemed to strip away all the pain and stress that had built up unknowningly."
    new "More than cool, the air almost seemed to strip away all the pain and stress that had built up unknowningly."

    old "The sound of flowing water continued to invite and tempt her further."
    new "The sound of flowing water continued to invite and tempt her further."

    old "As the cave narrowed, Sarah pressed and contorted her body through the slimming pathways."
    new "As the cave narrowed, Sarah pressed and contorted her body through the slimming pathways."

    old "Part of her feared becoming stuck, but it was nothing compard to the eagerness to find where it all led."
    new "Part of her feared becoming stuck, but it was nothing compard to the eagerness to find where it all led."

    old "Then, suddenly, the path opened up and Sarah stepped towards a small open space."
    new "Then, suddenly, the path opened up and Sarah stepped towards a small open space."

    old "Though it was underground, a soft glow of blueish light filled up the cave."
    new "Though it was underground, a soft glow of blueish light filled up the cave."

    old "The light danced as it sprung from the water, or reflected off it, Sarah wasn't sure."
    new "The light danced as it sprung from the water, or reflected off it, Sarah wasn't sure."

    old "Entranced by the sight, Sarah walked up closer towards the pool of water, and kneeled down besides it."
    new "Entranced by the sight, Sarah walked up closer towards the pool of water, and kneeled down besides it."

    old "The water was clear, but ran so deep, Sarah could not see the bottom."
    new "The water was clear, but ran so deep, Sarah could not see the bottom."

    old "Reflected slightly on the surface, she caught a glimpse of her own face."
    new "Reflected slightly on the surface, she caught a glimpse of her own face."

    old "What a mess she'd become."
    new "What a mess she'd become."

    old "Perhaps more than even the dirt and grime of the desert, Sarah worried about the darkened look in her eyes."
    new "Perhaps more than even the dirt and grime of the desert, Sarah worried about the darkened look in her eyes."

    old "Had her eyes always been so angry?"
    new "Had her eyes always been so angry?"

    old "Don't worry child. What is carved in, can be carved out."
    new "Don't worry child. What is carved in, can be carved out."

    old "Sarah flinched, turning instantly towards the source of the voice."
    new "Sarah flinched, turning instantly towards the source of the voice."

    old "Sitting in the corner of the cave, a man dressed in bandages."
    new "Sitting in the corner of the cave, a man dressed in bandages."

    old "Through the rags across his face, two gleeming eyes of black, peered out at her."
    new "Through the rags across his face, two gleeming eyes of black, peered out at her."

    old "Who are you!"
    new "Who are you!"

    old "The man made no motion suggesting he planned to move."
    new "The man made no motion suggesting he planned to move."

    old "No need to waste your time learning my name, child. I am of no importance, and I am not long for this world."
    new "No need to waste your time learning my name, child. I am of no importance, and I am not long for this world."

    old "A softness echoed through his voice. Sarah presumed he was male, but she could not be certain, so frail his body and so wrapped in gaze."
    new "A softness echoed through his voice. Sarah presumed he was male, but she could not be certain, so frail his body and so wrapped in gaze."

    old "I didn't come here for riddles."
    new "I didn't come here for riddles."

    old "A laughter, interbroken with a choking sound from his lungs could be heard throughout the cave."
    new "A laughter, interbroken with a choking sound from his lungs could be heard throughout the cave."

    old "We often find what we're not looking for."
    new "We often find what we're not looking for."

    old "He gestured around the cave."
    new "He gestured around the cave."

    old "You sought for water, and now you have found it. And perhaps a bit more."
    new "You sought for water, and now you have found it. And perhaps a bit more."

    old "Sarah watched the man, cornered in the shadow, the light danced all around the cave but seemed to avoid him."
    new "Sarah watched the man, cornered in the shadow, the light danced all around the cave but seemed to avoid him."

    old "Tell me who you are, or I'll make you tell me."
    new "Tell me who you are, or I'll make you tell me."

    old "Another broken laugh emerged from the ragged man."
    new "Another broken laugh emerged from the ragged man."

    old "How violent you have become over the years, my child. You used to be so gentle."
    new "How violent you have become over the years, my child. You used to be so gentle."

    old "Sarah narrowed her eyes."
    new "Sarah narrowed her eyes."

    old "You don't know me."
    new "You don't know me."

    old "I don't know you, but I have friends that do."
    new "I don't know you, but I have friends that do."

    old "And who might that be?"
    new "And who might that be?"

    old "Altyaehr, the Craftsman. Vaeda, the Birth-Mother. Naelyon, the Huntsman."
    new "Altyaehr, the Craftsman. Vaeda, the Birth-Mother. Naelyon, the Huntsman."

    old "My list of friends is long. Must I go on?"
    new "My list of friends is long. Must I go on?"

    old "Sarah recognized the names. Names from the pantheon of gods. In total, there were more than two-hundred names, but these were the most prominent names."
    new "Sarah recognized the names. Names from the pantheon of gods. In total, there were more than two-hundred names, but these were the most prominent names."

    old "I think I've heard enough."
    new "I think I've heard enough."

    old "A madman in a cave, rambling about his divine friends."
    new "A madman in a cave, rambling about his divine friends."

    old "Emerging from behind his cloth bindings, a smile of shattered teeth."
    new "Emerging from behind his cloth bindings, a smile of shattered teeth."

    old "Not a madman, only a messenger who has been waiting here for a long time to deliver it."
    new "Not a madman, only a messenger who has been waiting here for a long time to deliver it."

    old "Forgive me if my manners have failed over the years."
    new "Forgive me if my manners have failed over the years."

    old "Years?"
    new "Years?"

    old "Ooh, I can't say, but I suppose it must be close to two decades by now since I first came here."
    new "Ooh, I can't say, but I suppose it must be close to two decades by now since I first came here."

    old "Sarah only saw water here. Even with that, he couldn't have survived for that long out here."
    new "Sarah only saw water here. Even with that, he couldn't have survived for that long out here."

    old "That long, without food?"
    new "That long, without food?"

    old "The man gestured towards the pool of water."
    new "The man gestured towards the pool of water."

    old "The water provides all that I might need."
    new "The water provides all that I might need."

    old "Sarah wanted to dispute the man, but she couldn't deny that it was strange that he had survived here."
    new "Sarah wanted to dispute the man, but she couldn't deny that it was strange that he had survived here."

    old "It had been hard to get to this point, even with an entire army behind her, bringing supplies. The idea of one man managing to survive just for a few days..."
    new "It had been hard to get to this point, even with an entire army behind her, bringing supplies. The idea of one man managing to survive just for a few days..."

    old "How can you live off just water for two decades?"
    new "How can you live off just water for two decades?"

    old "A gift, from my friends. Or perhaps payment for my services now rendered."
    new "A gift, from my friends. Or perhaps payment for my services now rendered."

    old "Who knows, it's been so long living in this hollow world."
    new "Who knows, it's been so long living in this hollow world."

    old "The man smiled his broken smile again."
    new "The man smiled his broken smile again."

    old "Yes, it's been a long, long time since I came here."
    new "Yes, it's been a long, long time since I came here."

    old "Back when there were still caravans travelling these parts, few as they were."
    new "Back when there were still caravans travelling these parts, few as they were."

    old "My master, a great merchant, had a beautiful daughter, and she very much thought the same of me."
    new "My master, a great merchant, had a beautiful daughter, and she very much thought the same of me."

    old "But her father did not approve."
    new "But her father did not approve."

    old "Approved less when we acted upon our desires."
    new "Approved less when we acted upon our desires."

    old "Sarah watched the man pull his hand over his scalp, as if to soothe himself."
    new "Sarah watched the man pull his hand over his scalp, as if to soothe himself."

    old "Drove me out of the caravan, hunted me for a little bit, but then I suppose they decided the desert could finish what they failed to do."
    new "Drove me out of the caravan, hunted me for a little bit, but then I suppose they decided the desert could finish what they failed to do."

    old "I wandered the desert for a few days before I came upon this cave."
    new "I wandered the desert for a few days before I came upon this cave."

    old "As I entered, the water awaited me, and the voice spoke the words I needed to carry to you."
    new "As I entered, the water awaited me, and the voice spoke the words I needed to carry to you."

    old "Deep in the desert, no way out, but here I could live."
    new "Deep in the desert, no way out, but here I could live."

    old "The man shrugged."
    new "The man shrugged."

    old "Some would have chosen to die, but I suppose, I quite like being alive. And so I drink the water, and I am sustained."
    new "Some would have chosen to die, but I suppose, I quite like being alive. And so I drink the water, and I am sustained."

    old "Sarah's eyes drifted across his broken body. She wasn't sure if sustained was the right word."
    new "Sarah's eyes drifted across his broken body. She wasn't sure if sustained was the right word."

    old "You want me to believe the water is magical?"
    new "You want me to believe the water is magical?"

    old "The ragged man shook his head."
    new "The ragged man shook his head."

    old "Not magic. Divine."
    new "Not magic. Divine."

    old "Sarah sighed, frustrated at his obscurantism."
    new "Sarah sighed, frustrated at his obscurantism."

    old "I've had more than my fill of witchcraft and prophecies. If you have something to tell me, spit it out."
    new "I've had more than my fill of witchcraft and prophecies. If you have something to tell me, spit it out."

    old "The ragged man laughed again, his voice echoing through the cave."
    new "The ragged man laughed again, his voice echoing through the cave."

    old "Considering all, it is but a small message. A warning."
    new "Considering all, it is but a small message. A warning."

    old "Yes, my friends hold you in good favor. They look upon you with kindness and wish that you return to the path."
    new "Yes, my friends hold you in good favor. They look upon you with kindness and wish that you return to the path."

    old "The path?"
    new "The path?"

    old "Yes, the path."
    new "Yes, the path."

    old "I am on a path, towards a city. How is that not a path?"
    new "I am on a path, towards a city. How is that not a path?"

    old "They have lost sight of you."
    new "They have lost sight of you."

    old "You are special among specials, and they fear losing you more than most."
    new "You are special among specials, and they fear losing you more than most."

    old "I...are you talking about breaking the edicts of the gods?"
    new "I...are you talking about breaking the edicts of the gods?"

    old "Sarah knew the list, murder, lies, adultery, but by now she imagined she had broken more than a few of them."
    new "Sarah knew the list, murder, lies, adultery, but by now she imagined she had broken more than a few of them."

    old "The man laughed, again and again."
    new "The man laughed, again and again."

    old "No, child. Their edicts do not take hold on you."
    new "No, child. Their edicts do not take hold on you."

    old "They fear what all parents fear, to lose sight of their child. They urge you to turn away from this path to nothingness."
    new "They fear what all parents fear, to lose sight of their child. They urge you to turn away from this path to nothingness."

    old "Well, you've wasted a good deal of my time."
    new "Well, you've wasted a good deal of my time."

    old "I have no idea what any of this means, nor do I have any desire to find out."
    new "I have no idea what any of this means, nor do I have any desire to find out."

    old "I was burdened with carrying the words, not their meaning."
    new "I was burdened with carrying the words, not their meaning."

    old "The man leaned forward and pointed towards the water."
    new "The man leaned forward and pointed towards the water."

    old "However, there is also a gift."
    new "However, there is also a gift."

    old "For one who needs it."
    new "For one who needs it."

    old "The water?"
    new "The water?"

    old "It feeds body and soul. Grants sucor to those desperate and nourishes wounds and deeper wounds."
    new "It feeds body and soul. Grants sucor to those desperate and nourishes wounds and deeper wounds."

    old "Sarah looked towards the water."
    new "Sarah looked towards the water."

    old "They tell me you have a friend that might have need of it..."
    new "They tell me you have a friend that might have need of it..."

    old "Sarah's eyes went wide."
    new "Sarah's eyes went wide."

    old "How could you know that?"
    new "How could you know that?"

    old "Are you saying that this water will...heal Samayra?"
    new "Are you saying that this water will...heal Samayra?"

    old "I don't know what a Samayra is, but make them drink the water and the water will drive out all foulness."
    new "I don't know what a Samayra is, but make them drink the water and the water will drive out all foulness."

    old "Sarah fell to her knees by the pool and cupped the water into her hands."
    new "Sarah fell to her knees by the pool and cupped the water into her hands."

    old "Carefully, she poured some of it into a flask."
    new "Carefully, she poured some of it into a flask."

    old "Time..."
    new "Time..."

    old "Samayra was running out of time."
    new "Samayra was running out of time."

    old "I have to go!"
    new "I have to go!"

    old "We have no more words to barter. Take your gift and your warning. Do with each as you please."
    new "We have no more words to barter. Take your gift and your warning. Do with each as you please."

    old "And remember, we live in a hollow world."
    new "And remember, we live in a hollow world."

    old "Sarah turned and ran out of the cave."
    new "Sarah turned and ran out of the cave."

    old "With a second helping, Sarah poured some of the water onto her face and down her throat."
    new "With a second helping, Sarah poured some of the water onto her face and down her throat."

    old "Like a rush, she felt the stress and pain flow away from her body, her thirst quenched, appetite sated."
    new "Like a rush, she felt the stress and pain flow away from her body, her thirst quenched, appetite sated."

    old "Sarah became as once aware to the comfort of the absence of pain, as only those long trapped in it can be."
    new "Sarah became as once aware to the comfort of the absence of pain, as only those long trapped in it can be."

    old "Never had she imagined that simply feeling so much like herself, could be such a gift."
    new "Never had she imagined that simply feeling so much like herself, could be such a gift."

    old "I have to go."
    new "I have to go."

    old "Sarah turned and walked out of the cave."
    new "Sarah turned and walked out of the cave."

    old "Stepping out of the cave, Sarah saw the desert open back up before her."
    new "Stepping out of the cave, Sarah saw the desert open back up before her."

    old "Turning back around, she saw the lights of the camp just atop the hill."
    new "Turning back around, she saw the lights of the camp just atop the hill."

    old "Looking back down, she saw nothing but sand where the entrance to the cave should have been."
    new "Looking back down, she saw nothing but sand where the entrance to the cave should have been."

    old "Witchcraft..."
    new "Witchcraft..."

    old "Sarah muttered the word to herself as she began climbing back up the hill, trudging through the shifting sands of the dune."
    new "Sarah muttered the word to herself as she began climbing back up the hill, trudging through the shifting sands of the dune."

    old "With each step, Sarah could feel her legs sink further."
    new "With each step, Sarah could feel her legs sink further."

    old "But with each step, she reached forward, clawing her hands, digging deep into the sand and pulls herself up along the hill."
    new "But with each step, she reached forward, clawing her hands, digging deep into the sand and pulls herself up along the hill."

    old "A frenzy took hold of her as she continued her march, up and up the hill, faster and faster."
    new "A frenzy took hold of her as she continued her march, up and up the hill, faster and faster."

    old "Reaching over the ledge, Sarah toppled back into the camp."
    new "Reaching over the ledge, Sarah toppled back into the camp."

    old "She crawled back onto her feet, taking barely a moment to recover herself, and ran through the camp."
